node.text: The 35-year-old J.R. Smith is enrolling at North Carolina A&T State University to pursue a degree in liberal studies and also is waiting on the NCAA to sort out his eligibility so he can join the Aggies’ golf team.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 11, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and people playing football.

node.text: Former first-round pick Ha Ha Clinton-Dix is signing with the San Francisco 49ers, per his agents @_SportsTrust. 49ers’ safety Jaquiski Tartt still is recovering from a turf toe injury from last November.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 11, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and grass.

node.text: Ravens’ HC John Harbaugh said first-round pick Rashod Bateman will miss “a number of weeks” with the groin injury that he suffered at Tuesday’s practice.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and outdoors.

node.text: Colts quarterback Carson Wentz and guard Quenton Nelson are trending toward being available for Indianapolis' regular-season opener against the Seattle Seahawks, sources told ESPN’s Chris Mortensen.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 11, 2021. May be an image of 3 people.

node.text:
Colts have signed GM Chris Ballard and head coach Frank Reich each to contract extensions through the 2026 season, per ESPN’s Chris Mortensen.

Colts owner @jim.irsay clearly in a happy place with his leaders. Ballard was hired as GM in 2017. Reich was hired as HC in 2018.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and playing football.

node.text: Packers’ HC Matt LaFleur said today that Aaron Rodgers will “most likely not” play in the preseason. Jordan Love expected to get plenty of preseason play time.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and text that says 'COLT 4'.

node.text: Colts closed out today’s practice with rookie sixth-round pick Sam Ehlinger working as Indy’s starting QB. Today was the first day of camp in which Ehlinger took some reps with the Colts’ starters. Colts’ HC Frank Reich said Jacob Eason will start Sunday’s preseason game against Carolina, but he will split 1st team snaps with Ehlinger in the joint practices vs. the Panthers on Thursday and Friday.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 10, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

node.text: Lionel Messi and PSG have agreed to a two-year deal with an option for a third year. Messi now has arrived in Paris.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 10, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, people playing football and outdoors.

node.text: Patriots’ TE Hunter Henry is expected to miss “a couple of weeks” with the shoulder injury he suffered Sunday that is “not serious,” per source. It puts Henry on a timeline to be ready for the regular-season opener Sept. 12 vs. Miami.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 09, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, playing football and text that says 'COWBOTS BUCS EST.1960 1961 COWBOYS BUCCANEERS ppet Adam Schefter @AdamSchefter One month from tonight: Cowboys at Buccaneers.'.

node.text: Ready for some football…?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Adam Schefter on August 09, 2021. May be an image of football and text that says 'Ly Quest Diagnostics 263'.

node.text: Giants officially activated RB Saquon Barkley and LB Oshane Ximines from the Active/Physically Unable to Perform List. Barkley and Ximines will participate in their first training camp practice this afternoon.
